{"sections":{"main":{"type":"main-article","disabled":true,"settings":{"color_scheme":"","show_image":true,"enable_parallax":true,"image_size":"medium","content_width":"xs","show_date":false,"show_category":true,"show_author":false,"show_share_buttons":false,"show_sticky_bar":true,"toolbar_color_scheme":""}},"image_with_text_overlay_KBygTX":{"type":"image-with-text-overlay","name":"t:sections.image_with_text_overlay.presets.image_with_text_overlay.name","settings":{"color_scheme":"","image_size":"lg","image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Truffle_Risotto_Lifestyle_Image_FINE_WILD_UK_f7c8494e-da97-47d1-ac99-918944e2ea9d.jpg","mobile_image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Truffle_risotto_4.jpg","allow_transparent_header":false,"reveal_on_scroll":true,"remove_vertical_spacing":true,"content_width":"md","mobile_text_position":"place-self-center text-center","desktop_text_position":"sm:place-self-center sm:text-center","overlay_color":"#000000","overlay_opacity":0}},"prev-next-blog-posts":{"type":"prev-next-blog-posts","disabled":true,"settings":{"color_scheme":"","separate_section_with_border":false,"subheading":"","title":"Read more","show_category":true,"show_excerpt":true,"show_read_more":true}},"image_with_text_9db3y7":{"type":"image-with-text","blocks":{"richtext_PM4M4Q":{"type":"richtext","settings":{"content":"<h1>BLACK TRUFFLE RISOTTO<\/h1>"}},"subheading_h99brk":{"type":"subheading","settings":{"text":""}}},"block_order":["richtext_PM4M4Q","subheading_h99brk"],"disabled":true,"settings":{"color_scheme":"scheme-2","separate_section_with_border":false,"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/BLACK_TRUFFLE_RISOTTO_FINE_WILD_copy.jpg","reveal_on_scroll":true,"image_position":"end","content_width":"sm","remove_vertical_spacing":true}},"rich_text_K6d9VP":{"type":"rich-text","blocks":{"heading_f7EmrL":{"type":"heading","settings":{"text":"<strong>BLACK TRUFFLE RISOTTO<\/strong>","heading_tag":"h3"}},"subheading_EYmbMV":{"type":"subheading","settings":{"text":"<strong>SERVINGS:<\/strong> 2 <strong>PREP TIME:<\/strong> 30 MINUTES. <strong>COOK TIME:<\/strong> 45 MINUTES. <strong>TOTAL TIME:<\/strong> 1 HOUR, 15 MINUTES"}},"richtext_3KBEyM":{"type":"richtext","disabled":true,"settings":{"content":"<p>Use this text to share information about your brand with your customers. Describe a product, share announcements, or welcome customers to your store.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["heading_f7EmrL","subheading_EYmbMV","richtext_3KBEyM"],"settings":{"color_scheme":"scheme-2","separate_section_with_border":false,"content_width":"sm","text_position":"center","remove_vertical_spacing":false}},"rich_text_4KngPk":{"type":"rich-text","blocks":{"richtext_xLygbg":{"type":"richtext","settings":{"content":"<p>Fresh Truffles lend themselves perfectly to simple culinary preparations such as fresh pasta & risotto. This risotto recipe will help you to create the perfect backdrop for your fresh truffles to ensure maximum enjoyment.<\/p><p>A great risotto should have a slight bite to it, be luxurious, creamy, and gently fall outwards on the plate but not collapse.  Adding the stock gradually allows more stirring for the starches to be released from the rice, creating the lovely creamy consistency you are looking for.<\/p>"}},"richtext_iTRqaY":{"type":"richtext","settings":{"content":"<p><\/p><p><\/p>"}}},"block_order":["richtext_xLygbg","richtext_iTRqaY"],"settings":{"color_scheme":"scheme-2","separate_section_with_border":false,"content_width":"sm","text_position":"center","remove_vertical_spacing":false}},"image_with_text_AGg4Rz":{"type":"image-with-text","blocks":{"subheading_3Jqz9y":{"type":"subheading","settings":{"text":"<strong>Serves 2, as a Main Course<\/strong>"}},"heading_99Kr8c":{"type":"heading","settings":{"text":"<strong>INGREDIENTS<\/strong>","heading_tag":"h4"}},"richtext_QN73jt":{"type":"richtext","settings":{"content":"<ul><li>20g Fresh Black Truffle<\/li><li>1 Ltr (Approx.) Fresh Chicken or Vegetable Stock<\/li><li>180g Arborio Rice<\/li><li>2 Shallots Finely Chopped<\/li><li>1 Clove Garlic <\/li><li>1 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil<\/li><li>250 ml Dry White Wine<\/li><li>75g Butter, Diced<\/li><li>100g Finely Grated Parmesan<\/li><li>Salt & Pepper<\/li><\/ul>"}}},"block_order":["subheading_3Jqz9y","heading_99Kr8c","richtext_QN73jt"],"settings":{"color_scheme":"scheme-2","separate_section_with_border":false,"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Truffle_Risotto_ingredients_3bb9101d-74e3-4696-a9f8-bd242dce36a6.jpg","reveal_on_scroll":true,"image_position":"start","content_width":"sm","remove_vertical_spacing":true}},"multi_column_VJkQL8":{"type":"multi-column","blocks":{"image_with_text_hxcanR":{"type":"image_with_text","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Truffle_Risotto_Step_1_FINE_WILD_UK_3c301c9f-8e2d-4afb-b07e-3166fdb16607.jpg","title":"<strong>STEP ONE<\/strong>","heading_tag":"h4","content":"<p>Bring the stock to the boil in a saucepan then keep on a low simmer. Using a heavy-based, flat-bottomed pan, sweat the shallots and garlic in the olive oil with a pinch of salt over moderate heat until soft and translucent.  Add the rice to the pan and heat through until all grains are hot, lightly toasted without colour and become sticky.<\/p>","link_url":"","link_text":""}},"image_with_text_4nP9Ur":{"type":"image_with_text","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/IMG_0006_1_5e7fcab8-58e1-4301-a603-574d4acdef18.jpg","title":"<strong>STEP TWO<\/strong>","heading_tag":"h4","content":"<p>Turn up the heat and add the wine to the rice and stir until almost completely reduced, then add 1 third of the hot stock, again stirring until absorbed. Lower the heat to moderate.<\/p>","link_url":"","link_text":""}},"image_with_text_mLx4Np":{"type":"image_with_text","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Truffle_-_Risotto_bcd95c31-05ad-4199-b4cb-38b039fc721d.jpg","title":"<strong>STEP THREE<\/strong>","heading_tag":"h4","content":"<p>Keep stirring in small quantities of stock and allowing it to be almost totally absorbed until the rice is just cooked, this will take approximately 15 minutes from adding the wine.  You may not need all of the stock to achieve this.  The rice should be al dente but not chalky and you should be able to drag a spoon through the pan and the risotto gently flow back.<\/p>","link_url":"","link_text":""}},"image_with_text_GLXt6a":{"type":"image_with_text","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Truffle_risotto.jpg","title":"<strong>STEP FOUR<\/strong>","heading_tag":"h4","content":"<p>Turn off the heat, add the diced butter and parmesan, pepper, salt (if needed) and quickly beat into the risotto until you get a creamy consistency. The rice will keep absorbing liquid so it is important to let it rest for a minute or so before serving. This will allow you to add a touch more hot stock if needed.<\/p>","link_url":"","link_text":""}}},"block_order":["image_with_text_hxcanR","image_with_text_4nP9Ur","image_with_text_mLx4Np","image_with_text_GLXt6a"],"settings":{"color_scheme":"scheme-2","separate_section_with_border":false,"columns_per_row":2,"stack_on_mobile":true,"overlap_image":false,"content_alignment":"center","text_alignment":"center","spacing":"sm","subheading":"","title":"<strong>METHOD<\/strong>","content":""}},"image_with_text_RcpbaV":{"type":"image-with-text","blocks":{"subheading_Q9UdKG":{"type":"subheading","settings":{"text":"SERVE IN WARM BOWLS AND SHAVE  THE TRUFFLE AT THE TABLE IN FRONT OF GUESTS TO ENJOY MAXIMUM AROMA & THEATRE"}},"heading_FpGxGN":{"type":"heading","disabled":true,"settings":{"text":"Image with text","heading_tag":"h1"}},"richtext_zEwYGB":{"type":"richtext","disabled":true,"settings":{"content":"<p>Use this text to share information about your brand with your customers. Describe a product, share announcements, or welcome customers to your store.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["subheading_Q9UdKG","heading_FpGxGN","richtext_zEwYGB"],"settings":{"color_scheme":"scheme-2","separate_section_with_border":false,"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_i